{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkMonitorSignalName\/notifyNetworkAvailable","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/networkmonitorsignalname\/notifynetworkavailable"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Case","role":"symbol","title":"NetworkMonitorSignalName.notifyNetworkAvailable","externalID":"s:3GIO24NetworkMonitorSignalNameO06notifyB9AvailableyA2CmF","symbolKind":"case","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"notifyNetworkAvailable"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkMonitorSignalName"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Whether the network is considered available. That is, whether the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"system has a default route for at least one of IPv4 or IPv6."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"notifyNetworkAvailable","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Real-world networks are of course much more complicated than","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this; the machine may be connected to a wifi hotspot that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"requires payment before allowing traffic through, or may be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connected to a functioning router that has lost its own upstream"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connectivity. Some hosts might only be accessible when a VPN is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"active. Other hosts might only be accessible when the VPN is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not active. Thus, it is best to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_network_monitor_can_reach()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_network_monitor_can_reach_async()"},{"text":" to test for reachability","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on a host-by-host basis. (On the other hand, when the property is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", the application can reasonably expect that no remote"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"hosts at all are reachable, and should indicate this to the user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in its UI.)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See also [NetworkMonitor](\/\/documentation\/gio\/networkmonitor\/onnetworkchanged(flags:handler:)."}]}]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/NetworkMonitorSignalName/notifyNetworkAvailable":{"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"notifyNetworkAvailable"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Whether the network is considered available. That is, whether the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"system has a default route for at least one of IPv4 or IPv6.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"NetworkMonitorSignalName.notifyNetworkAvailable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkMonitorSignalName\/notifyNetworkAvailable","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/networkmonitorsignalname\/notifynetworkavailable"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/NetworkMonitorSignalName":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/networkmonitorsignalname","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"NetworkMonitorSignalName","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkMonitorSignalName","title":"NetworkMonitorSignalName","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkMonitorSignalName","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"}}}